{
  "doc_id": "41531",
  "text": "Patient recruitment. We prospectively recruited 8 adults (aged ≥16 years) who had sustained TBI and needed intracranial monitoring, sedation, muscular paralysis, intubation and mechanical ventilation. Patients were treated in Neuro-intensive care using our standard TBI management protocols [CITATION_1] . Targeted depth of sedation was not changed over the study period. Sedation was achieved with propofol, with or without midazolam. Barbiturates were not used. Electroencephalography and bispectral index were not measured as they are not routinely used in our unit. Written, informed assent was provided by patients' relatives, and the study was carried out in conformation with the spirit and the letter of the Declaration of Helsinki. The protocol was approved by the National Research Ethics Service (NRES) Committee East of England -Cambridge Central (REC Reference No. 11/EE/0463).",
